<section xml:id="sec-fas-3-practice">
	<title>Deliberate Practice: Adding and Subtracting Fractions</title>
    <p>
        Algebra is a skill, which means it requires practice to become proficient. But it will take more than rote
        repetition to get there. Deliberate practice is the thoughtful repetition of a task. For each of these sections,
        you will be given a list of specific skills or ideas to focus on as you practice thinking through the problems.
    </p>
	<p>
		<em>Focus on these skills:</em>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<p>
					Write the original expression. 
				</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p>
					Show the multiplication for the common denominator step. 
				</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p>
					Try to use the least common denominator rather than applying the general formula. 
				</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p>
					Present your work legibly. 
				</p>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</p>
    <worksheet xml:id="sec-fas-3-worksheet">
		<p>
			<em>Instructions:</em> Perform the indicated calculation.. 
		</p>
		<exercise>
			<p>
				Calculate <m>\displaystyle \frac{7}{12} + \frac{11}{18}</m>. 
			</p>
		</exercise>
		<exercise>
			<p>
				Calculate <m>\displaystyle \frac{13}{10} - \frac{7}{25}</m>. 
			</p>
		</exercise>
		<exercise>
			<p>
				Calculate <m>\displaystyle \frac{5x}{4y} + \frac{8y}{3x}</m>. 
			</p>
		</exercise>
		<exercise>
			<p>
				Calculate <m>\displaystyle \frac{4a}{3b^2} - \frac{2}{7ab}</m>. 
			</p>
		</exercise>
		<exercise>
			<p>
				Calculate <m>\displaystyle \frac{6}{5p^2q} + \frac{2q}{3p}</m>. 
			</p>
		</exercise>
		<exercise>
			<p>
				Calculate <m>\displaystyle \frac{4}{7x^2 y} - \frac{3x}{2y^2}</m>. 
			</p>
		</exercise>
		<exercise>
			<p>
				Calculate <m>\displaystyle \frac{3n^2}{m^3} + \frac{4m}{3n^2}</m>. 
			</p>
		</exercise>
		<exercise>
			<p>
				Calculate <m>\displaystyle \frac{4}{xy} + \frac{3}{x^2z}</m>. 
			</p>
		</exercise>
		<exercise>
			<p>
				Calculate <m>\displaystyle \frac{5a}{3b^2 c^3} - \frac{4c}{7b^2}</m>. 
			</p>
		</exercise>
		<exercise>
			<p>
				Calculate <m>\displaystyle \frac{3mn}{5p^2} + \frac{5m^2}{8n^2 p}</m>. 
			</p>
		</exercise>
	</worksheet>
</section>
